@optional {page_number: int=1 # **Deprecated** - This field has been deprecated and we will stop supporting it completely in a future release. Please use "next_page_token" for pagination instead of this field.  The page number of the current page in the returned records., search_key: str # User name or email address of a user. If this parameter is provided, only the SIP phone system integration enabled for that specific user will be returned. Otherwise, all SIP phones on an account will be returned., page_size: int # The number of records returned within a single API call., next_page_token: str # The next page token is used to paginate through large result sets. A next page token will be returned whenever the set of available results exceeds the current page size. The expiration period for this token is 15 minutes.}
@returns(200) {next_page_token: str, page_count: int, page_number: int, page_size: int, phones: [map], total_records: int} # **HTTP Status Code:** `200`<br>
SIP Phones listed successfully.

**Error Code:** `200`<br>
Permission missing: Enable SIP Phone Integration by contacting a Zoom Admin first.
@errors {400: **HTTP Status Code:** `400`<br> Bad Request

}

@endpoint POST /sip_phones
@desc Enable SIP phone
@required {authorization_name: str # Authorization name of the user  registered for SIP Phone., domain: str # The name or IP address of your provider’s SIP domain. (example: CDC.WEB)., password: str # The password generated for the user in the SIP account., proxy_server: str # IP address of the proxy server for SIP requests. Note that if you are using the UDP transport protocol, the default port is 5060. If you are using UDP with a different port number, that port number must be included with the IP address. If you are not using a proxy server, this value can be the same as the Register Server., register_server: str # IP address of the server that accepts REGISTER requests. Note that if you are using the UDP transport protocol, the default port is 5060. If you are using UDP with a different port number, that port number must be included with the IP address., user_email: str(email) # The email address of the user to associate with the SIP Phone. Can add [.win, .mac, .android, .ipad, .iphone, .linux, .pc, .mobile, .pad] at the end of the email (ex. user@test.com.mac) to add accounts for different platforms for the same user., user_name: str # The phone number associated with the user in the SIP account., voice_mail: str # The number to dial for checking voicemail.}
@optional {proxy_server2: str # IP address of the proxy server for SIP requests. Note that if you are using the UDP transport protocol, the default port is 5060. If you are using UDP with a different port number, that port number must be included with the IP address. If you are not using a proxy server, this value can be the same as the Register Server, or empty., proxy_server3: str # IP address of the proxy server for SIP requests. Note that if you are using the UDP transport protocol, the default port is 5060. If you are using UDP with a different port number, that port number must be included with the IP address. If you are not using a proxy server, this value can be the same as the Register Server, or empty., register_server2: str # IP address of the server that accepts REGISTER requests. Note that if you are using the UDP transport protocol, the default port is 5060. If you are using UDP with a different port number, that port number must be included with the IP address., register_server3: str # IP address of the server that accepts REGISTER requests. Note that if you are using the UDP transport protocol, the default port is 5060. If you are using UDP with a different port number, that port number must be included with the IP address., registration_expire_time: int=60 # The number of minutes after which the SIP registration of the Zoom client user will expire, and the client will auto register to the SIP server., transport_protocol: str(UDP/TCP/TLS/AUTO) # Protocols supported by the SIP provider.<br> The value must be either `UDP`, `TCP`, `TLS`, `AUTO`., transport_protocol2: str(UDP/TCP/TLS/AUTO) # Protocols supported by the SIP provider.<br> The value must be either `UDP`, `TCP`, `TLS`, `AUTO`., transport_protocol3: str(UDP/TCP/TLS/AUTO) # Protocols supported by the SIP provider.<br> The value must be either `UDP`, `TCP`, `TLS`, `AUTO`.}
@returns(201) **HTTP Status Code:** `201`<br>
SIP Phone Created.

@errors {400: **HTTP Status Code:** `400`<br>
Bad request.<br>
**Error Code:** `200`<br> Permission missing: Enable SIP Phone Integration by contacting a Zoom Admin first.<br>
**Error Code:** `300`<br>SIP Phone with the same email already exists.


, 404: **HTTP Status Code:** `404`<br>
**Error Code:** `1001`<br> User {userId} not exist or not belong to this account.


}

